INSERT INTO bytes.bytes (id, author_id, title, body, code_snippet, language, embedding, type, is_active, created_at, updated_at) VALUES (
  '432aec3e-b968-4986-b86f-0e58a0623ae8',
  '00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000001',
  $escape$LangChain Streaming — Token-by-Token Output and UX Patterns That Actually Work$escape$,
  $escape$LangChain's LCEL makes streaming first-class — every `Runnable` exposes `.stream()` and `.astream()` out of the box, yielding `AIMessageChunk` objects as tokens arrive. Passing `streaming=True` to `ChatOpenAI` (or any chat model) enables true token-level output; without it, `.stream()` still works but buffers until the full response completes.

For granular control in complex chains — RAG pipelines, agents — use `astream_events(version="v2")`. It emits structured events (`on_chat_model_stream`, `on_retriever_end`, `on_tool_end`) so you can differentiate token chunks from retrieval results, letting you update distinct UI regions independently.

Key UX pattern: pipe streamed chunks into a `ReadableStream` on the server, then consume with `fetch()` and `response.body.getReader()` on the client. Never buffer the full response before rendering — it kills perceived latency. For Next.js, pair LangChain's `HttpResponseOutputParser` with the Vercel AI SDK's `StreamingTextResponse` for encoding handled automatically.

One gotcha: intermediate `RunnableLambda` steps returning non-string types silently break streaming unless you yield chunks explicitly or wrap with `RunnablePassthrough`.$escape$,
  $escape$from langchain_openai import ChatOpenAI
from langchain_core.prompts import ChatPromptTemplate

llm = ChatOpenAI(model="gpt-4o", streaming=True)
prompt = ChatPromptTemplate.from_template("Explain {topic} concisely.")
chain = prompt | llm

# Sync: yields AIMessageChunk objects
for chunk in chain.stream({"topic": "transformers"}):
    print(chunk.content, end="", flush=True)

# Async: granular events for complex chains
async for event in chain.astream_events({"topic": "transformers"}, version="v2"):
    if event["event"] == "on_chat_model_stream":
        print(event["data"]["chunk"].content, end="", flush=True)$escape$,
  $escape$python$escape$,
